[Maps of Myanmar can be seen at http://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/map/myanmar_map2.htm and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3934329,10628.

Maungdaw is a district of the coastal Rakhine State in western Myanmar located on the Bay of Bengal (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maungdaw_District) bordered by Bangladesh to the northwest. The town of Maungdaw, with a population of 400 000 in 2008, is the westernmost city of Myanmar and borders Bangladesh; the majority of the populace, about 80 percent, are said to be stateless Muslims of the Rohingya minority group (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maungdaw). A map of Rakhine State showing the location of Maungdaw can be found at https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/8e/Rakhine01.png.

For a discussion of pneumonia, please see my moderator comments in prior ProMED-mail posts below. Further information concerning this outbreak would be welcomed from knowledgeable sources. - Mod.ML

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3934329,10628.]
